Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place in skillet. Add onion; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is browned, turning once. Remove chicken from skillet; set aside. Add balsamic vinegar; cook 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in peaches and drained tomatoes. Return chicken to skillet. Cover, reduce heat and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in centers (165 degrees F). Sprinkle with basil just before serving.